  "prompt": "How are style fonts added to an MIT app inventor?",
  "response": "In MIT App Inventor, you can add custom fonts through a few different methods:\n\n1. Through Screen Properties:\n- Go to the Properties panel\n- Look for the \"FontTypeface\" property\n- You can select from predefined options or choose \"Custom\"\n\n2. Using Custom Font Files:\n- Upload your font file (.ttf or .otf) to the project\n- Go to the \"Media\" section\n- Add the font file\n- Reference the font in your code or design\n\n3. Programmatically:\n- Use the SetFont method\n- Example: Component.SetFont(Typeface.CreateCustomTypeface(\"YourFontName\"))\n\n4. Text Component Settings:\n- Select a text component\n- In the Properties panel, modify the \"FontTypeface\" property\n- Choose \"Custom\" and select your uploaded font\n\nImportant Tips:\n- Font files must be .ttf or .otf format\n- Make sure you have the right to use the font\n- Font files are added to the project's media folder\n- Test thoroughly to ensure font displays correctly\n\nRemember that font support can vary slightly depending on the device and Android version.",
